cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the integration of spectrum-sharing technology into cellular systems, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new cooperative paradigm for relaying transmission in spectrum-sharing cellular systems, which involves information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper focuses on improving spectrum efficiency in cellular systems through spectrum sharing and cooperative relaying, which falls under the domain of communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for spectrum sharing cellular networks, which involves systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions delay-tolerant wireless services with asymmetric downlink/uplink traffics, such as data streaming, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
